Brazilian Stock Movers: Cia. Hering, Embraer Rise; Gol Plunges

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-07-29T20:29:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/brazilian-stock-movers-cia-hering-embraer-rise-gol-plunges.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index climbed 0.2 percent to 58,823.45.  Cia. Hering (HGTX3 BS) gained 1.5 percent to 33.24 reais.
 Brazil ’s fourth-largest retailer reported second-quarter net
income of 77.3 million reais ($49.6 million), an 81 percent
increase from a year earlier, according to a regulatory filing.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) surged 7.2 percent to 11.21 reais.
The world’s fourth-largest planemaker said second-quarter net
income increased to 153.8 million reais from 101.7 million reais
a year earlier. The mean estimate of three analysts compiled by
Bloomberg was 102 million reais.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)   (GFSA3 BS) jumped 4.5 percent to 7.50 reais. The
homebuilder led gains by companies that depend on domestic
demand as traders cut bets for higher borrowing costs in Brazil.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS) plunged 22
percent to 12 reais. The airline had its recommendation cut at
Banco BTG Pactual SA, Credit Suisse Group AG and Bank of America
Corp. after it reduced some of its 2011 forecasts.  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS) dropped 1.4 percent to 45.61 reais. The
world’s largest iron-ore producer said in a filing second-
quarter net income rose to $6.45 billion from $3.71 billion a
year earlier. Vale was expected to post profit on an adjusted
basis of $1.39 a share, the average of 13 estimates compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
